# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
You have initial state which is positive. Iterate through the array. 
- Ignore all positive numbers
- When you see 0, immediately return 0
- If it is negative, swap the sign of the state  

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(N) in the worst case
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
/**
 * @param {number[]} nums
 * @return {number}
 */
var arraySign = function(nums) {
    // initial state
    let isNeg = false;
    // iterate through the array
    for(let num of nums) {
        if(num === 0) return 0;
        // swap the sign
        if(num < 0) isNeg = !isNeg;
    }
    return isNeg?-1:1;
};
```

