# Intuition
If you go on to multiply each value and check the answer at last then checking the constraints you will get a overflow error for sure.

We have to find a solution without computing the entire values.

# Approach
First sort the entire vector and the ittitare till you find a positive or 0. Keep counting the number of occurances of negative values, if you encounter a zero then directly return 0 otherwise if count of negative is even then return 1 or else return -1.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
- O(nlogn)

- Space complexity:
- O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int arraySign(vector<int>& nums) {
        sort(nums.begin(),nums.end());
        int neg=0;
        int pos=0;
        for(int i=0;i<nums.size();i++)
        {
            if(nums[i]==0)
            {
                return 0;
            }
            else if(nums[0]>0)
            {
                return 1;
            }
            else{
                if(nums[i]>0)
                {
                    break;
                }
                neg++;
            }
        }
        if(neg%2==0)
        {
            return 1;
        }
        else{
            return -1;
        }
    }
};

```

