solutions.content:
```

/*  
We don't need to multiple all elements and then check the product, it will give RTE

To avoid this, we just need to check for each element is it +ve, -ve or 0.
And depending on this we just need to update our sign variable,

if the element is < 0 : multiple sign by -1,
if element == 0 :  multiply sign by 0
else the only condition that left is, if element is > 0 : multiply sign by 1( can skip this condition)

At the end just return the sign
*/

class Solution {
public:
    int arraySign(vector<int>& nums) {
        int sign = 1;
        for(int x : nums) sign *= (x == 0) ? 0 : ((x < 1) ? -1 : 1);
        return (sign < 0) ? -1 : ((sign > 0) ? 1 : 0);
    }
};
```

