# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Brute force approach will be to multiply all numbers and then see whether product is 0, positive or negative.

__BUT__ on a closer inspection it can be seen that the numbers that affect the naswer are the ones that are less than equal to 0, Positive number don't change the sign of the product
> -4 * 2 = -8.
0 * 2 = 0
4 * 2 = 8
__Whatever sign of the first term was, is continued when multiplied with a positive number, hence we dont really need to know how many positives do we have in the array.__

__Two observations are needed to solve this question__

>__1)__ If an element in the array is 0, product will be 0, no need   to multiply anything anymore, that how powerful 0 is here!!
__2)__ If the number of negative integers in the array, the answer be negative, else positive

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
>1) Traverse the array/vector
>2) Check if the element is 0 or not
>> If the element is 0, the answer or product will stay 0, no matter what is multiplied to it now, therefore return 0

>3) Check if the number is negative
>>If the number is negative track the frequency of the negative numbers
Else Continue

>4) If in Nothing has been return so far, check if the frequency of the negatives is odd 
>> If, yes : return -1
Else Return 1

