# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
If we know winner of n - 1 friends, we can easily know the winner of n friends.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Take the example as n = 5 and k = 3:
if only 1 person had been there, then winner = 1
now 2nd person comes, move two times: 1 -> 2 -> 1 -> 2 winner = 2
now 3rd person comes, move two times: 1 -> 2 -> 3 -> 1 winner = 1
now 4th person comes, move two times: 3 -> 4 -> 1 -> 2 winner = 2
now 5th person comes, move two times: 1 -> 2 -> 3 -> 4 winner = 4


# Complexity
- Time complexity: **O(n)**
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: **O(1)**
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

