In this problem it can be clearly seen we need to divide it into further subproblems.
Hence recursive approach is mostly followed.
First, we need to find the kth element.
It can be simply found by the formula `(k+start)%n` where start is the position to start counting.
Since this position changes after every pass we will follow a reverse recursive approach i.e. implement recursion in a way such that the functional calls when popped from stack simulate the entire procedure.
Thus, we will keep the base condition to return 0 so that the start initially is 0.
And then calculate.
The code is as follows :
```
    class Solution {
        public int findTheWinner(int n, int k) {
            return helper(n,k)+1;
        }
        public int helper(int size, int k){
            if(size==1)return 0;
            return (helper(size-1,k)+k)%size;
        }
    }
```
