solutions.content:
We have following recursive structure - 

1. If last member remaining - **return 1**.
2. Recurse for remaining n - 1 members. Just `findTheWinner(n-1, k)` would mean that we are starting from 0. So, we adjust the new position by adding `k - 1` (denotes that we skip *`k - 1`* players) and modding with `n` for wrap-around. `+1` in the below equation accounts for the index starting from 1 and not from 0. 
	So final recursive equation becomes - **`1 + findTheWinner(n - 1, k) + k - 1) % n`**

```
int findTheWinner(int n, int k) {
	return (n == 1 ? 1 : 1 + (findTheWinner(n - 1, k) + k - 1) % n);
}
```

