1. Fill an ArrayList with the numbers from 1 to n.
2. Return a helper function.
3. The helper function takes a list of integers as argument, k and current k (current k is the value which has to be dropped from the game).
4. Update the current k, with the value that has to be dropped and call the recursion function until you are left with only one element in the arraylist and return it. 
```
class Solution {
    public int findTheWinner(int n, int k) {
        List<Integer> lis = new ArrayList<Integer>();
        for(int i=1; i<=n; i++){
            lis.add(i);
        }
        return helper(lis, k, 0);        
    }
    private int helper(List<Integer> lis, int k, int curr){
        if(lis.size()==1){
            return lis.get(0);
        }
        //int cur = 0;
        curr = (curr+k-1)%lis.size();
        //k=k%lis.size();
        lis.remove(curr);
        return helper(lis, k, curr);        
    }
}
```

