solutions.content:
`dp[i][j]`: the min jump to arrive at lane `j` at point `i`

Since the frog starts at lane 2, the initial states should be,
`dp[0][2] = 0`, 
`dp[0][1] = 1`,
`dp[0][3] = 1`.

This is an space `O(1)` solution.
```
class Solution {
    public int minSideJumps(int[] obstacles) {
        int n = obstacles.length;
        //dp[i][j]: the min jump to arrive at lane j at point i
        int[] dp = new int[4];
        dp[1] = dp[3] = 1;
        for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
            int y = obstacles[i];
            int[] temp = new int[4];
            for (int j = 1; j <= 3; j++) {
                if (j == y) {
                    temp[j] = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
                } else {
                    temp[j] = dp[j];
                }
            }
            //get the min at point i for all 3 lanes
            int min = Math.min(temp[1], Math.min(temp[2], temp[3]));
            for (int j = 1; j <= 3; j++) {
                if (j == y) continue;
                //update dp[i][j]
                temp[j] = Math.min(min+1, temp[j]);
            }
            dp = temp;
        }
        return Math.min(dp[1], Math.min(dp[2], dp[3]));
    }
}
```

