[🎨  The ART of Dynamic Programming](https://leetcode.com/discuss/general-discussion/712010/The-ART-of-Dynamic-Programming-An-Intuitive-Approach%3A-from-Apprentice-to-Master): It is more natural for me to switch the rows and columns, ie. let `dp[i][j]` denote the minimum side-steps performed to reach cell `i`,`j`.  The goal is to reach the `N`<sup>th</sup> row at minimum cost.  This bottom-up solution first attempts to perform optimal side-steps for the previous `i - 1`<sup>th</sup> row by optimally side-stepping from each column `j` to each column `k` (an astute observer will notice when `j == k`, this minimum operation is a no-op, since `min(x, x) == x`).  Then use those optimal solutions of the previous `i - 1`<sup>th</sup> row to formulate the optimal solutions of the current `i`<sup>th</sup> row until the `N`<sup>th</sup> row is reached.  Then we return the minimal value of the `N - 1`<sup>th</sup> row as the best answer.

---

**Kotlin Solutions:**

1. Create the bottom-up solution
```
class Solution {
    fun minSideJumps(A: IntArray): Int {
        var INF = (1e9 + 7).toInt()
        var N = A.size
        var dp = Array(N){ IntArray(3){ INF } }                                 // 🤔 memo
        dp[0][1] = 0                                                            // 🛑 base case
        for (i in 1 until N) {
            var x = A[i - 1] - 1                                                // pre obstacle 🍎 at pre row i - 1
            var y = A[i] - 1                                                    // cur obstacle 🍏 at cur row i
            for (j in 0..2) {
                // best 👈 👉 side-hops from col j -> k for pre row i - 1:
                if (j != x)                                                     // 🚫 disclude possibility due to pre obstacle 🍎 at col j
                    for (k in 0..2)
                        dp[i - 1][j] = Math.min(dp[i - 1][j], 1 + dp[i - 1][k]) // 💰 +1 penalty for side-hops from col j -> k
                // best 👇 forward-hops from pre row i - 1 -> cur row i
                if (j != y)                                                     // 🚫 disclude possibility due to cur obstacle 🍏 at col j
                    dp[i][j] = Math.min(dp[i][j], dp[i - 1][j])                 // 💰 no penalty for forward-hops from pre row i - 1 -> cur row i
            }
        }
        return dp[N - 1].min()!!                                                // 🎯 minimum 👈 👉 side-hops to reach row N - 1
    }
}
```

