class State{
    int jumps;
    int index;
    int lane;
    State(){
        this.lane = 2;
    }
    State(int j, int i, int l){
        this.jumps = j;
        this.index = i;
        this.lane = l;
    }
}
class Solution {
    public int minSideJumps(int[] obstacles) {

        Queue<State> q = new LinkedList<State>();
        boolean[][] vis = new boolean[4][obstacles.length];
        q.offer(new State(0,0,2));

        while(!q.isEmpty()){
            int size = q.size();
            while(size-- > 0){
                //Get current state
                State front = q.poll();

                //Check if we are at the end of the road
                if(front.index == obstacles.length-1){
                    return front.jumps;
                }

                //Check if we are obstructed or check if this is visited already
                if(obstacles[front.index] == front.lane || vis[front.lane][front.index]){
                    continue;
                }

                //Visit current lane by marking it visited
                vis[front.lane][front.index] = true;


                //Add all other options from this state to next state
                for(int i=1;i<=3;i++){

                    //Moving/Hopping to next index in same lane
                    if(i == front.lane){
                        q.offer(new State(front.jumps, front.index+1, i));
                    }
                    //Exploring sideways jumps also
                    else{
                        q.offer(new State(front.jumps+1, front.index, i));
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        //No route till end of the road, Not possible in this question I guess
        return -1;
    }
}
```
**Time Complexity:** We are visiting every possible position on the road for the frog, 
							O(No. of lanes * length of the lane(obstacles)) = O(3 * N)
**Space Complexity:** O(4 * N), for keeping track whether each position is visited or not,
													using 4 instead of 3 as the rows of vis[][] is 4, to handle 1-indexed
													lanes.

