av_lanes represents the lanes we could potentially be travelling on, we start of with {2} because we know that we start on lane 2. however when we need to switch lanes, we remove the current lane we are travelling on and add the other two potential lanes to the set. This means if the other two lanes are available then we are travelling on both of them at the same time untill we hit an obstacle, then our quantum state collapses and we only have one lane we can travel on untill we hit an obstacle and have to jump. hope you enjoy this little joke.

```
class Solution:

    def minSideJumps(self, obstacles: List[int]) -> int:
        jumps=0
        av_lanes={2}
        for idx,v in enumerate(obstacles):
            if v in av_lanes and len(av_lanes)<2:
                jumps+=1
                av_lanes={1,2,3}-{av_lanes.pop(),obstacles[idx-1]}
            elif v in av_lanes:
                av_lanes.remove(v)
        return jumps
