class Solution {
    //All possible directions to go up and down. Some could become invalid which we will check
    int[] directions = new int[]{1, 2, -1, -2};

    public int minSideJumps(int[] obstacles) {
        //We will this array to eleminate solving sub problems repetedly
        int[][] memo = new int[obstacles.length][4];
        //-1 represents no value found
        for(int[] m : memo) {
            Arrays.fill(m, -1);
        }
        //let's solve by dfs
        return dfs(obstacles, 0, 2, memo);
    }

    private int dfs(int[] obstacles, int curPoint, int lane, int[][] memo) {
        //we are one point behind n and there wont be any obstacles in n as problem defins. So we can stop here
        if(curPoint+1 == obstacles.length) {
            return 0;
        }

        //We already calculatted this, so just return
        if(memo[curPoint][lane] > -1) {
            return memo[curPoint][lane];
        }

        int result;
        if(obstacles[curPoint+1] != lane) { //We can move to next point since there is no blocker
            result = dfs(obstacles, curPoint+1, lane, memo);//Moved to next point in same lane
        } else {
            //There is blocker so we need to go to other lane in same point
            result = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
            for(int jumpDir : directions) {
                int newLane = lane + jumpDir;
                //Check if it is within lane 1-3 and that has no blocker
                if(1 <= newLane && newLane <= 3 && obstacles[curPoint] != newLane) {
                    result = Math.min(result, 1+dfs(obstacles, curPoint, newLane, memo)); //jumped to different lane in same point
                }
            }
        }

        //Remeber this best decession for the given point and lane
        memo[curPoint][lane] = result;
        return result;
    }
}
```

