solutions.content:
## Understanding the logic

The idea is to create a table storing the minimum side jumps required to reach a particular lane of a particular index.

Suppose index is denoted by i (0 <= i < obstacle.length) and lane is denoted by j (1, 2, 3).
dp[i][j] denotes the minimum side jumps to reach index i and lane j
To find the value of dp[i][j] there are 3 different paths from the previous index(i-1) to reach [i][j].
**dp[i][j] = Math.min(path1, path2, path3)**

Initially I am assigning **dp[i][j] = Infinity**; when there is an obstacle present at index i, lane j. To preserve the obstacle data I am simply adding dp[i][j] with itself.**Hence, dp[i][j] = dp[i][j] + Math.min(path1, path2, path3)**

**Example: say, i = 3; j = 1
then path1 = dp[i-1][1] + 0 side jump (since we are not changing lanes)
path2 =  dp[i-1][2] + 1 side jump (if there is no obstacle at [i][2]); else + 2 side jumps
path3 = dp[i-1][3] + 1 side jump (if there is no obstacle at [i][3]); else + 2 side jumps**


## Code
```
let minSideJumps = function (obstacle){
	let dp = new Array (obstacle.length);
	for(let i = 0; i < obstacle.length; i++){
		dp[i] = new Array(4).fill(0);
		dp[i][obstacle[i]] = Infinity;
	}
	// Initial State
	dp[0][1] = 1;
	dp[0][2] = 0;
	dp[0][3] = 1;
	for(let i = 1; i < dp.length; i++){
		for(let j = 1; j < 4; j++){
			value1 = j === 1 ? dp[i-1][1] : (obstacle[i] === 1 ? dp[i-1][1]+2 : dp[i-1][1]+1)
			value2 = j === 2 ? dp[i-1][2] : (obstacle[i] === 2 ? dp[i-1][2]+2 : dp[i-1][2]+1)
			value3 = j === 3 ? dp[i-1][3] : (obstacle[i] === 3 ? dp[i-1][3]+2 : dp[i-1][3]+1)
			dp[i][j] += Math.min(value3, value2, value1);
		}
	}
	return Math.min(...dp[dp.length-1]);
}
```

