solutions.content:
*First, let us discuss the recursive formula:*
Let us assume that we are on point i and currently in lane "curr".Let the function be f
**Base Case:**
if i==obstacles.size()-1
	 we simply return 0 since it is given that last point has no obstacles.
**Now,**
*if (i+1)th point in the curr lane is safe, we will simply move ahead*
     thus, we return f(i+1,curr)
else
   we have two options( the adjacent lanes).
   lets denote answer to be res. lets set res=INT_MAX.
   we will check if we can make a side jump to these lanes now ( i.e we look if they are obstacle free at point i). If we are able to perform side jump, we make res=min(res,1+f(i+1,safe adj lane)
   So we explore both adjacent lanes and return res.

**Memoization**
Now if we draw a computation tree( we can see overlapping subproblems), try it out on paper. Thus, we use memoization.

**Time Complexity**
