solutions.content:
`dp[i][j]`  How many sideway jumps at point i and lane j
1. If `obstacle[i] == j + 1` means we have obstacle in point i and lane j. We cannot jump to this point, so `dp[i][j] = Integer.MAX_VALUE`
2. Else we can reach this point i and lane j.
- From the same lane, `dp[i][j] = dp[i - 1][j]` no need for jump
- From the other two lanes, `obstacles[i] != (j + 1) % 3 + 1` is to make sure, the obstacle is not front of point i - 1 and lane `(j + 1) % 3`(different from current line). 
For example, if we current in point 1 and lane 1, if obstacle is in point 1 and lane 2, we cannot jump directly from point 0 lane 2 to point 1 lane1. We have to route to the other lane 3 to see if it can reach lane 1 or not.
```
class Solution {
    public int minSideJumps(int[] obstacles) {
        int n = obstacles.length;
        int[][] dp = new int[n][3];
        for (int[] d : dp) {
            Arrays.fill(d, Integer.MAX_VALUE);
        }
        dp[0][1] = 0;
        dp[0][0] = 1;
        dp[0][2] = 1;
        for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < 3; j++) {
                if (obstacles[i] == j + 1) { // cannot reach
                    continue;
                }
                if (dp[i - 1][j] != Integer.MAX_VALUE) { // same lane
                    dp[i][j] = Math.min(dp[i][j], dp[i - 1][j]);
                }
				// from other lanes, make sure the point i and lane k, h does not have obstacle
                if (dp[i - 1][(j + 1) % 3] != Integer.MAX_VALUE && obstacles[i] != (j + 1) % 3 + 1) {
                    dp[i][j] = Math.min(dp[i][j], dp[i - 1][(j + 1) % 3] + 1);
                }
                if (dp[i - 1][(j + 2) % 3] != Integer.MAX_VALUE && obstacles[i] != (j + 2) % 3 + 1) {
                    dp[i][j] = Math.min(dp[i][j], dp[i - 1][(j + 2) % 3] + 1);
                }
            }
        }
        return Math.min(dp[n - 1][2], Math.min(dp[n - 1][1], dp[n - 1][0]));
    }
}
```

