# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We need to reach the end of the lane by minizing side jumps. Hence at each i keep track of number of jumps required to reach lane 1, 2, 3. Note difference between no of jumps between any 2 nodes cannot exceed 1.  

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
I kept 3 variables to keep track of jumps. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minSideJumps(vector<int>& o) {
        int n=o.size();
        int a=1, b=0, c=1, ta, tb, tc, inf=5*1e5;
        if(o[0]==1){
            a=inf;
        }
        if(o[0]==3){
            c=inf;
        }
        for(int i=1; i<n; i++){
            if(o[i]==1){
                ta=inf;
                tb=min(b, c+1);
                tc=min(c, b+1);
            }else if(o[i]==2){
                ta=min(a, c+1);
                tb=inf;
                tc=min(c, a+1);
            }else if(o[i]==3){
                ta=min(a, b+1);
                tb=min(b, a+1);
                tc=inf;
            }else{
                ta=min(a, min(b+1, c+1));
                tb=min(b, min(a+1, c+1));
                tc=min(c, min(a+1, b+1));
            }
            a=ta;b=tb;c=tc;
        }
        return min(a, min(b, c));
    }
};
```

