# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
- dp[i] memorizes the number of mininum side jumps to the cuurent point
- dp[i]==INT_MAX if there is a stone (1,2,3)
- update the blocked value if  there is no stone (0)

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minSideJumps(vector<int>& v) {
        vector<int> dp{1,0,1};
        int last=0;
        for(auto n:v){
            if(n==0) {
                if(last==0) continue;
                dp[(last+2)%3]=1+min(dp[(last+3)%3],dp[(last+4)%3]);
                last=0;continue;
            }
            vector<int> ndp(3);
            int i=(n+2)%3, j=(n+3)%3, k=(n+4)%3;
            ndp[i]=INT_MAX;
            ndp[j]=min(dp[j],dp[k]==INT_MAX?INT_MAX:dp[k]+1);
            ndp[k]=min(dp[k],dp[j]==INT_MAX?INT_MAX:dp[j]+1);           
            dp=ndp;
            last=n;
        }
        return *min_element(dp.begin(),dp.end());
    }
};
```

