```
We keep 3 Balanced Set for lower K values in MaxHeap, upper K values in MinHeap and
mid range values in MidHeap. Also we store the values in a queue so that we can remove
previous element of latest M elements from those Set. Track the count of added elements
and also track the sum of mid range elements in MidHeap.

We store the lower K values in MaxHeap and as soon as MaxHeap size > K we remove
top element and insert in to MinHeap which contains upper K values. If MinHeap size > K
then the top value of MinHeap is obviously in the mid range and so we add it to the
MidHeap and add its value to running sum.

Incase of removing previous element, we search it in MaxHeap and MinHeap.
If target is in MaxHeap then we remove it from MaxHeap and insert the smaller element
from MidHeap, means the smallest mid range value which can be a lower K element
and also update running sum and MidHeap. Incase of MinHeap we insert the largest 
value from MidHeap which can be a higher K element and update the running sum and
MidHeap. Otherwise, the target element is in MidHeap and we just remove it from
MidHeap and update running sum.
